    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-18T02:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-18T02:30:00-05:00" n="311"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">661.91/7–1850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-18T13:00:00+05:30"
                            >July 18, 1950—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 18—8:31 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Bajpai SYG <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss> called me noon today to say
                    Soviet Government Moscow had published texts of recent exchange of notes with
                        <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> without securing consent of latter.
                    Bajpai added that he hoped that US government would not release either message
                    until after agreement between the two governments for simultaneously release in
                    Washington and Delhi. He referred to press report to effect US planned release
                    messages at time delivery and said he thought this report must be
                    inaccurate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
